{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"72546919-4cdf-48d2-96e7-f1088933ace1","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. I can't review your specific workflow, but here's what you need to change to switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. **NuGet.org setup**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new trusted publisher policy linking your GitHub repo, branch/tag filter, and workflow file path\n\n### 2. **Workflow changes**\n\n**Add `id-token` permission:**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n```yaml\n# BEFORE (API key):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER (trusted publishing):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nWith trusted publishing the `dotnet` CLI automatically picks up the OIDC token from the `ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_URL` / `ACTIONS_ID_TOKEN_REQUEST_TOKEN` environment variables — no API key needed.\n\n### 3. **Clean up**\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository secrets once verified.\n\nWould you like me to edit a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f02a9e05-8083-4841-a937-cffd3adcab95","outputTokens":347,"requestId":"0FC7:C2AE2:17D7B48:1AFEB90:69E81A67"},"id":"ce1242a9-8807-4229-b84e-84cd0d644b23","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:39.826Z","parentId":"9876ad27-40e7-4cb8-bbe2-361d097743bc"}
